# Reliable Data Transmission

This project explores the fundamental concepts behind reliable digital communication inspired by Ben Eater’s explanation of data transmission systems.

## Topics Covered
- Binary data transmission
- Clock synchronization
- Shared ground reference
- Signal timing
- Noise and transmission errors
- Error detection basics
- Reliable communication principles

## Key Idea
Reliable communication is not just about sending data, but ensuring the receiver correctly interprets the transmitted information despite timing issues and noise.

## Applications
- Computer networks
- Embedded systems
- Serial communication
- Error correction systems
- Quantum communication fundamentals
